JALINGO – Governor Darius Ishaku has expressed the determination of his administration to make Taraba state the number one producer of rice in Nigeria. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Gov Ishaku disclosed this during a courtesy call on the Ambassador of the Republic of Belarus, Mr Vyacheslav Bril at the country’s Nigerian Embassy in Abuja. Gov Ishaku,who was at the embassy to seek ways in which that country and Taraba state can collaborate for the development of the state, briefed his host on the development strides already achieved by his administration during his first tenure. He called for assistance of the Belarusian government in areas of education, health, skills acquisition and transportation. He said his administration’s dry season farming has boosted rice production tremendously and created many wealthy farmers in the state. He expressed the desire to do a lot more to get more youths in the state productively engaged and taken out of the unemployment queue